The paper deals with game theoretic solution concepts and their learnability from data, which falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.SC). Within cs.SC, the most relevant sub-category is game theory (cs.GT), which is the study of strategic interactions between agents. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the learnability of solution concepts, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper applies its methods to various economic domains, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with cooperative games and optimal auction design, which are sub-fields of computational economics (cs.EC).
